# -*- html -*-
Notes on Industrial Collaboration

     <div class="row gutters">

      <div class="column-15">

	<p>I have had much experience with
	collaboration between university and
	  industrial/government organizations.</p>
	<p>In all
	cases, the key to success was to take the
	time to learn the needs and social
	  structures of the organizations.</p>
	<p>For examples of this process, see below.</p>
	
	<h3>Verification of industrial processes</h3>
	
	<img class="blackimg" align=right src="img/lexisnexis.png">
	<p>I am exploring, with an
           industrial partner (LexisNexis) issues
           related to the cost-effective exploration
           and deployment of models generated by
           data miners for Big Data applications.</p>
        <p>This new lab, called “SeBig” (Software
           Engineering for Big Data) focuses on
           the validation of Big Data inference in
          industrial applications.</p>
	<p>Initially,
           we are  explore the certification and
           possible improvement of text mining
           methods for legal
           applications. Subsequent work will be
           adapted, according to earlier results.
           Research is conducted in an agile
           manner with a backlog of industrial-based
           problems being explored by graduate
           students in monthly sprints, monitored by
           faculty with daily scrums.
	</p><br clear=all>

	<center><iframe
		   src="http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/key/f8etbZ448ukfOs"
