	<h3>STTR: Small Business Technology Transfer 	</h3>
	
	<img class="blackimg" align=right src="img/gtech.png">
	<p>With Grammatech, I have previously proposed, developed, won, and
	  completed,  a $750,000  stage II Dod SBIR/STTR.</p>
	<br clear=all>
	<p>For more details, click here:<br>
	  <a href="img/sttr-gt.png">
	    <img align=middle width=250 src="img/sttr-gt.png"></a></p>
	
	<h3>Research management	</h3>
	
	<img class="blackimg" align=right src="img/nasa.png">
	<p>I worked for four years inside the firewalls of
	  the NASA Software Assurance research program. There, I
	  was a technical consultant to NASA civil servant as they decided
	  how to allocated millions of dollars in research dollars
	  to research centers.	</p><br clear=all>
	
	<h3> Research programmers/ interns</h3>

	<p>In many cases, I have managed teams of graduate students
	  performing programming tasks for industrial clients.</p>
	<p>Two approaches for this are:
	  <ul>	<img class="blackimg" align=right src="img/jpl.gif">
	    <li><em>Term projects:</em> During term time, my students often
	      develop tools that implement cutting-edge algorithms
	      for industrial clients. For example, for the Jet Propulsion
	      Laboratory, my programmers have developed state-of-the-art
	      effort estimation tools.
	    </li>
	    <li><em>Summer interns:</em>  many of my students spend their
	      summer working for industrial clients. When requested,
	      I assist/guide in the management of those students
	    (site visits, regular teleconfs).</li>
	</ul></p><br clear=all>
      </div>
     </div>






 
